  "body": "<!--NOTE: -->\r\n<!--- General questions should go to the discord chat instead of the issue tracker.-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nDuring initial sync, the light-client server errors with\r\n\r\n```\r\nError: finalityHeader not available 0xbfd6e68ea9ab8be2665a8662743e82ee0a72f846182fdf6232f9ff1a4bac9854\r\n    at LightClientServer.getFinalizedHeader (/usr/app/node_modules/@chainsafe/lodestar/src/chain/lightClient/index.ts:511:13)\r\n    at LightClientServer.maybeStoreNewBestPartialUpdate (/usr/app/node_modules/@chainsafe/lodestar/src/chain/lightClient/index.ts:474:28)\r\n    at LightClientServer.onSyncAggregate (/usr/app/node_modules/@chainsafe/lodestar/src/chain/lightClient/index.ts:453:5)\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\n- The light-client server should not prepare updates during sync\r\n- finalityHeader may not be available and it's not an issue, it's just that the node hasn't seen that finality header",
